      • getResult

        public ItemStack getResult(IInventory input,
                           World world,
                           RecipeType<?> type)
        Automatically returns a result from the first recipe that matches this inv and type. Modders should probably not use this, and instead use getRecipe(IInventory, World, RecipeType) since you get the recipe object itself.
        Parameters:
        input - An inventory.
        world - The world.
        type - The type of recipe to match against.
        Returns:
        The output of the first matching recipe, or ItemStack.EMPTY if no recipes match.

      • getRecipe

        @Nullable
public <T extends IRecipe> T getRecipe(IInventory input,
                                                 World world,
                                                 RecipeType<T> type)
        Used to find a matching recipe for the given inv, world, and type. Since this requires an IInventory, modders can use RecipeWrapper to avoid direct implementation. For crafting recipes, it is advised to still use InventoryCrafting. The dynamic vanilla recipes require they be crafted in one.
        Parameters:
        input - An inventory.
        world - The world.
        type - The type of recipe to match against.
        Returns:
        The first matching recipe.

      • getRemainingItems

        @Deprecated
public NonNullList<ItemStack> getRemainingItems(IInventory input,
                                                            World world,
                                                            RecipeType<?> type)
        Deprecated. 
        Modders should not use this if possible. In the context that this is used, you should already have the recipe. Do not run extra lookups using this method. Use IRecipe.getRemainingItems(IInventory).
